# Dec 24 â€“ Security Groups

## What is a Security Group?

A stateful virtual firewall controlling inbound and outbound traffic.

## Key Properties

- Stateful
- Attached to ENIs
- Allow rules only

## Why Security Groups Matter

They are the first line of cloud defense.

## Security Group vs ufw

| Aspect | Security Group | ufw |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Location | AWS edge | OS level |
| Type | Stateful | Stateful |
| Default | Deny inbound | Deny inbound |
| Scope | Instance | Host |

## Architect Insight

Security Groups replace traditional host firewalls at scale.

Cloud firewalls protect before traffic reaches the OS.
OS firewalls protect after traffic reaches the host.
